By bringing citi bike to the island, residents would benefit hugely with this new transportation method that is greener and safer (The island already have car-free lanes that are perfect for future bike lanes). This would also bring more live and activities to the island. I'm surprised that citi bike didn't start from the island, which should have been the perfect practice field for bikeshare and biking commutes.
